node.title: Tommy Fury pulls out of Jake Paul fight
node.alt: Tommy Fury in a blue robe before a fight
node.description: Tommy Fury says he has been forced to withdraw from his upcoming fight with YouTuber-turned-boxer Jake Paul due to a severe chest infection and a broken rib.
node.content: ["Tommy Fury, the half-brother of heavyweight champion Tyson Fury, says he has been forced to withdraw from his upcoming fight with YouTuber-turned-boxer Jake Paul due to a severe chest infection and a broken rib.", "Fury was\u00a0due to face Paul on December 18 in Tampa, Florida.", "He won on the undercard of Paul's August fight against former UFC welterweight champion Tyron Woodley.", "Fury comes from a long line of boxers but has also looked to grow his celebrity outside the sport and appeared on the British reality show Love Island in 2019.", "\"I am absolutely heartbroken that I have been forced to withdraw from my fight with Jake Paul due to a bacterial chest infection and broken rib,\" the 22-year-old said in a tweet posted by his promoter Frank Warren.", "\"I can't express how disappointed I am and I really do hope we can get this fight rescheduled in the New Year, I want this fight to still happen more than anything.\"", "With Fury pulling out, Paul said he would have a rematch with Woodley.", "Paul and Woodley's cruiserweight fight in August ended in a split-decision victory for Paul.", "\"I am giving him [Woodley]\u00a0$US500,000 ($710,000) extra if he can knock me out,\" Paul said in a video on Twitter.", "Reuters"]
